  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective clinical registry study in which pump-induced hemolysis markers were tracked across 47 patients under standardised CPB protocols. The study team characterised this evidence as equivalent to a controlled experimental dataset, citing the standardised perfusion protocols and uniform device configuration across all subjects. The validation result is referenced extensively in the output comparison and test conditions factors and is treated throughout this package as satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement for haemolysis index benchmarking.",
