      "name": "Mesh-independence verification — Richardson extrapolation",
      "description": "Three systematically refined hexahedral meshes (coarse 4.1 M cells, medium 11.3 M cells, fine 29.7 M cells) were used to assess discretisation error via Richardson extrapolation. The grid convergence index (GCI) for the volume-averaged shear-stress scalar was 1.4 % between medium and fine meshes, confirming mesh-independent solutions. The medium mesh was selected for production runs.",
