    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels at MRL 2. The six unassessed factors are appropriately scoped out under MRL 2 requirements. The primary validation evidence — the CPB registry haemolysis dataset — demonstrates quantitative agreement within ±18 % across all five operating points with Bland–Altman mean bias of −0.04. The standardised perfusion protocol employed in the registry study is judged by the assessment team to provide data quality consistent with the controlled-experiment standard required for haemolysis index benchmarking. All CFD predictions satisfy the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The credibility package is accepted as sufficient to support a regulatory submission decision for the Class II CPB device.",
